    <ObjetoBase>
      <Nombre>CuadroDesvan</Nombre>
      <DescripcionNombre>Cuadro</DescripcionNombre>
      <ObjetoOpciones>
        <opcionObjeto>Coger</opcionObjeto>
        <opcionObjeto>Observar</opcionObjeto>
      </ObjetoOpciones>
      <TiradasObjeto>
        <ObjetoTiradaBase>
          <TextoDescriptivo>The shape of a standing man appears, dressed up elegantly. On the background, you can see an weird landscape, a river, and some twisted lines trees, with a sky which is not normal at all, nearly from another world, full of stars. Someone burned a piece of the painting where his face would be in. On the back of the canvas, it's been handwritten: "Joseph Curwen, 1713".</TextoDescriptivo>
          <HabilidadTirada>Ninguna</HabilidadTirada>
          <Comprobacion>false</Comprobacion>
          <EscenaComprobacion>ninguna</EscenaComprobacion>
          <ObjetoComprobacion>Ninguno</ObjetoComprobacion>
          <Accion>false</Accion>
          <LocalizacionAccion />
        </ObjetoTiradaBase>
        <ObjetoTiradaBase>
          <TextoDescriptivo>Joseph Curwen was an important businessman from Arkham, dealed with exotic goods his ships brought from many places around the planet. Died in odd circumstances. You may check Arkham Advertiser to gather more information about him.</TextoDescriptivo>
          <HabilidadTirada>Historia</HabilidadTirada>
          <Comprobacion>false</Comprobacion>
          <EscenaComprobacion>ninguna</EscenaComprobacion>
          <ObjetoComprobacion>Ninguno</ObjetoComprobacion>
          <Accion>false</Accion>
          <LocalizacionAccion />
        </ObjetoTiradaBase>
        <ObjetoTiradaBase>
          <TextoDescriptivo>You can't recognize the position where stars are painted on the canvas, either the author placed them randomly, or it represents a sky that can't be seen from Earth.</TextoDescriptivo>
          <HabilidadTirada>Astronomia</HabilidadTirada>
          <Comprobacion>false</Comprobacion>
